  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency winterization assistance in Hirat and Zabul</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will provide emergency winterization assistance to 3,500 of the most vulnerable households in Hirat (3000 households) and Zabul (500 households), closely coordinated with the ES/NFI cluster. Assistance will be through standard package for heating and fuel ($200) with eligible beneficiaries also referred to DRC protection assistance (funded under other projects as well as proposed under AHF 6RA), including case management and referrals. DRC will identify beneficiaries through its existing HEAT datasets as well as through HEAT data collected through ongoing JAT assessments (coordinated through the OCT) participation in joint winterization needs assessments organized by the ES/NFI cluster and joitn selection of beneficiaries through already collected IDP profiling data (Hirat). All beneficiary selection criteria and beneficiary lists will be agreed with the ES/NFI cluster to ensure the response is well-coordinated and in Hirat, DRC will implement a joint response with NRC in Sharak Sabz.</narrative>
  </description>
